tect Edda Tarn as she swaps in Rift quartz to straighten the note.\",\n        \"Mediate between the Bonewrights and the Saltglass Syndicate or choose a side when passion hardens to threat; identify the foreign cullet resonance woven into the Gate’s subchord, extract the thread without shattering the frame, and secure signed testimony from witnesses that the Gate was deliberately tampered with for profit.\"\n      ],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\"speaker\": \"Matron Sere Kall\", \"lines\": \"Bone remembers what it bears, and this city has leaned upon these ribs for three centuries with grief and grace alike. We tune the Gate in daylight so that every ear can judge whether the wind lies, and so that no ledger may later claim the song was private or convenient. Stand with us, Rogan Kettlebone, as a wall that does not move when coin shouts or when law pretends that ink is heavier than water. I do not ask you to draw your blade unless theirs gleams first, but I ask your presence to weigh the air toward honesty and away from theater. Today we set quartz into truth and truth into memory, and if anyone brings a false note to our door, we will hold it up to the sun until even mirrors stop reflecting it.\"},\n        {\"speaker\": \"Edda Tarn\", \"lines\": \"I have listened to the Gate until sleep itself hummed wrong, and I hear a bubble in the throat of its song that should not exist if the frame were left alone. This shard from the Rift of Lumes carries a patient, even tone, and if I seat it gently, the hum will straighten like a spine released from a bad chair. If my hand slips, the frame will scream like bone caught in frost, and the Watch whistles will answer whether they are invited or not. I am not afraid of my work, but I am afraid of hands that jostle because they think a craftswoman is a lever they can pull to change a city’s vote. Guard my reach, Rogan, and I will make the Gate speak without guilt, and I will swear to what I hear in words that no court can sh