, their shadows lengthening in peace. Veyla extracts the filament and hands it to you with a flourish that tells the onlookers they have seen a trick undone rather than performed, and the thread’s uneasy music confirms the point. Watch quills scratch as five, then seven, then ten witnesses sign their names and trades, testimonies careful and plain so that no judge can excuse them as poetry. Matron Sere Kall speaks the Conclave’s public debt to you like a bell, the Watch nods grimly at your chain as if remembering the better parts of you, and Veyla Prism offers to guide you into the Saltglass Expanse, remarking that a city that keeps its records in daylight deserves a navigator who does the same.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"connections\": {\"previous\": [\"M4\"], \"next\": [\"M6\"]},\n      \"rewards\": [\n        {\"type\": \"item\", \"description\": \"Cullet Thread: a coil of glass filament that still hums with the tuned frequency of the false note, incontrovertible key evidence that the Gate’s subchord was tampered for profit and a compass to the hand that plucked it.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"reputation\", \"description\": \"Public debt of thanks from Matron Sere Kall: the Conclave acknowledges your stand in open yard, granting you usable leverage with Bonewrights on permits, bridges, and construct aid when you next call.\"},\n        {\"type\": \"ally\", \"description\": \"Veyla Prism: the glassborn artisan agrees to guide you into the Saltglass Expanse, her eyes trained to hear light and her hands sure where dunes sing and wyrms dream.\"}\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"